✅ 1. Check System Requirements
•	Windows 10/11 (64-bit)
•	1.64 GB free disk space
•	Git for Windows (required)
________________________________________
✅ 2. Install Git
Flutter needs Git.
Steps
1.	Go to: https://git-scm.com/download/win
2.	Install with default settings
3.	After install → Restart computer (recommended)
________________________________________
✅ 3. Download Flutter SDK
1.	Go to official Flutter download page:
https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/windows
2.	Download flutter_windows_x.x.x-stable.zip
3.	Extract it to a folder (example):
4.	C:\src\flutter
________________________________________
✅ 4. Add Flutter to PATH
So you can run Flutter commands from anywhere.
Steps:
1.	Press Windows + R → type sysdm.cpl → Enter
2.	Go to Advanced → Environment Variables
3.	Under System Variables, select Path → Edit
4.	Click New and add:
C:\src\flutter\bin
5.	Click OK to save.
________________________________________
✅ 5. Verify Flutter Installation
Open Command Prompt or PowerShell and run:
flutter --version
If Flutter version shows, it is installed correctly.
________________________________________
✅ 6. Run Flutter Doctor
This checks missing requirements.
flutter doctor
You will see something like:
•	✔ Flutter SDK
•	✔ Dart SDK
•	❗ Android toolchain missing
•	❗ Chrome missing
•	❗ Android Studio not installed
Follow any instructions that Flutter Doctor shows.
________________________________________
✅ 7. Install Android Studio (Required for Android Apps)
1.	Download: https://developer.android.com/studio
2.	Install with default settings
3.	Open Android Studio → go to SDK Manager
4.	Install:
o	Android SDK
o	Android SDK Platform
o	Android Virtual Device (AVD)
Run again:
flutter doctor
1b
void main() {
  int a = 10;
  int b = 20;
  int sum = a + b;

  print("Sum = $sum");
}
